  "source_notes": "Sy Scholfield quotes from various Swedish newspapers including ''Blekingsposten'', Friday, 1 March 1861, page 2: \"... för H. K. H. hertiginnans af Östergöthland lyckliga nedkomst med en Prins i Onsdags kl. ¾ till 11 e.m.\" (Translation: the Duchess happily gave birth to a Prince on Wednesday at three-quarters before 11 PM).\\n\\nPreviously, Scholfield speculated 9 PM, quoting from ''Altonaer Nachrichten'', 3 March 1861, p. 3: \"Stockholm, vom 28. Februar, (pr. Tel.) Die Herzogin von Ostgothland ist geftern Abend von einem Sohne entbunden worden, der die Namen Karl Oscar Wilhelm und den Titel Herzog von Westgothland erhalten hat.\"\\n(Stockholm, 28 February, (pr[ivate] Tel[egram]) The Duchess of Ostgothland was delivered last night of a son who received the name Karl Oscar Wilhelm and the title Duke of Westgothland). A time of 9pm is speculative.\\n",
